The taste is of fruitier rose water. It is a bright, crisp, clear taste redolent
of the Spring for which it's named. On the finish, a bold note of grapefruit or
orange juice resonates clearly. It's amazing and almost like candy; very easy to
drink. The can's description of _Graprefruit & Blossom_ is surprisingly accurate
to the drink's taste. Red Bull consistently amazes me with its depth and
complexity; compared to many others, Red Bull makes other companies' efforts to
create a fruity and bright profile for the medium feel half-assed at most.

Compared to this past season's [[2024 Winter Edition Iced Vanilla
Berry|Red_Bull_Winter_Edition_Iced_Vanilla_Berry]] this one bats just below for
me in terms of personal favorites. But it's not bad. Very good actually. Very
very good.

